By Our Correspondent The Presidency has announced that President Muhammadu Buhari will on Tuesday, March 30, proceed to London, the United Kingdom, for a routine medical check-up.  Prior to the trip, the President will meet with Security Chiefs first in the morning, after which he will embark on the journey to London.  A terse statement by the Special Adviser to the President (Media and Publicity), Femi Adesina, said President Buhari is due back in the country in the second week of April, 2021.